gomodel:SYNGO_4009  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"TMEM16F / Anoctamin-6 could be a post-synaptic component of C-boutons\"\n\nSeveral experiments in Fig 2 show that TMEM16F protein is an alfa-motoneuron marker, which faces cholinergic C-boutons synapses.\n- \"By staining TMEM16F was observed in choline acetyltransferase-positive (ChAT+) motoneurons, specifically located in the ventral horn laminae VIII and IX. This protein can be observed forming clusters at the plasma membrane of soma and dendrites (Figs. 2A and B)\"\n- \"Co-staining of TMEM16F with a plasma membrane marker of motoneurons (Na+/K+-ATPase alfa1) is shown in (Fig. 2F) verifying its localization.\nIn Fig 2G, TMEM16F protein is observed on the opposite side to the presynaptic marker Synaptophysin, which could indicate a postsynaptic localization, although strong evidence would be necessary.\nMoreover, TMEM16F clusters are found facing the vesicular acetylcholine transporter (VAChT) pre-synaptic clusters (Fig. 2I), being VAChT a marker of synaptic cholinergic C-boutons.. Experimental description: 2-month-old wild-type C57BL/6J mice" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099699 replaced by GO:0097060" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9888-0928" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2345-393X" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4009" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

